				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd like to see a game do leveling like a MUD I played.  The did RE-Morting.  You could hit Max level (109) fairly quickly, but you would open up new classes and new races by Re-Morting.  
<br />

<br />
Re-Morting or Re-Mortalizing means you start over as a level 1.
<br />

<br />
When you Re-Morted you could keep on skill/spell from the previous class.  So cleric could keep a heal and then Re-Mort as a melee class.
<br />

<br />
Every higher Re-Mort class had innate skills and higher stat caps, so Re-Mort 1 races made you a little tougher, but not remarabley so that they were over powered.
<br />

<br />
There were three Tiers of Re-Morts good evil and neutral races with each Tier have three levels of Re-Morts.  
<br />

<br />
Once you went all the way through each Tier of Remorts you would then qualify for the final Re-Mort race - Dragon.
<br />

<br />
All equipment had required levels so a Re-Morted level 1 couldn't weear god gear.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway - Re-Morting rocked.  One would really revist old areas and low level equipment never went out of need because people were always Re-Morting.  Some did it just because they were bored and liked leveling.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />  And because there were so many levels and you leveled so quickly you were always being rewarded.
<br />

<br />
Note:  This was a voluntary PvP MUD, though there were SOME PvP areas.
<br />

<br />
I'd play a well done Re-Mort game in a sec.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Mezrin Kortex</span> 75 Entrancer <span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=605959&amp;resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Profile</a></span>  &lt;---Guild Leader of <span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.asa-tru.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Asa-Tru</a></span>
