				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The MuD sounds similiar to FFXI, you don't have to reach max level to &quot;start&quot; again at level 1 with a new job, but you get to keep all skill caps and flags from your other job (but not spells and abilities). I think the ffxi job system is one of the coolest things not found in other games. Making alts does'nt feel like a waste of time away from your main because it's still helping out your main job. 
<br />

<br />
It also does something that I'm not sure was totally intentional but it keeps the low level game alive. I signed into the game a few months back and the lowbie areas were almost as busy as 3 years before when the game was still new to the US. You got to a place like crushbone in eq1 and the place is deserted, even in eq2 the lowbie areas are'nt near as populated. If theres one thing I could ask for in all mmos it would be the ability to change jobs on your main character and then change back.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=648576" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.idiosynk.com/personal/misc/sig.jpg" border="0" /></a>
